<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1437,1352,1938]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Posterior tip of sternohyoideus 16.0%, sternohyoideus-heart gap 0.02, heart 4.6% (MP = 18.7%), snout-heart interval 21.0%, heart-liver gap 7.3%, liver lobes multipartite, right liver 37.8% (MP = 47.1%) with 34 segments, left liver 36.3% (MP = 47.5%) with 39 segments, liver nearly symmetrical, anterior liver extension 0.03, posterior liver tail 0.01, left liver = 0.96 right liver, liver overlaps gall bladder gap by 0.4%, gall bladder 1.5% (MP = 66.4%), right ovary 3.1% (MP = 77.5%), left ovary 2.3% (MP = 79.4%), right adrenal MP = 78.6%, left adrenal MP = 79.8%, right kidney 5.7% (MP = 83.8%), left kidney 5.7% (MP = 86.1%), kidney overlap (0.43), kidney-vent interval 19.1%, kidney-vent gap 11.1%, rectal caecum 1.9%, maximum diameter equal to that of adacent small intestine, caecum-vent interval 14.1%.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1437,1352,1938]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Respiratory system lacking tracheal lung and left lung complex, trachea 19.1% (MP = 11.5%) with an estimated 152 tracheal rings or 83.0 rings/10% SVL, anterior lung tip 18.7%, cardiac lung 2.3%, tracheal entry terminal, right lung 27.1% (MP = 34.5%) with several tiers of faveoli along cranial third of lung, followed by a single tier of ediculae along medial fifth of lung, and trabecular parenchyma along caudal half of lung, posterior tip at 48.1% with terminal 3.8% forming a double folded tail, bronchus 18.7%, posterior tip of bronchus 39.7%, bronchus = 0.69 right lung, trachea-bronchus 37.8% (MP = 20.8%), total lung 29.4% (MP = 33.4%).</paragraph>
